<TITLE> UK anticipates free, fair polls </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 3 (bdnews24.com)  The United Kingdom is sanguine that the Dec. 18 general elections would be free and fair, participated by all political parties, its envoy said on Monday. It also sees the phased easing of emergency to facilitate polls campaign as "positive". "We will provide all types of cooperation to the elected government coming through the election," British high commissioner to Bangladesh Stephen Evans said. He spoke to reporters after meeting with BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia in her Gulshan office in the evening. Evans said he discussed various issues of bilateral interests with Khaleda in his first-ever courtesy meeting with the former prime minister. Present among others in the meeting were BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain, former foreign affairs adviser Riaz Rahman and the BNP chief's foreign affairs coordinator and former foreign secretary Shamsher Mobin Chowdhury. "We have historic ties with Britain," Chowdhury said. He added the BNP chief discussed with the high commissioner ways to boost socio-economic relationship between the two countries. Asked if the ensuing election came up on the agenda, Chowdhury said, "We talked nothing about the elections with the diplomats," adding that demands had been placed before the government. BNP chairperson's information officer Maruf Kamal was also present at the briefing. bdnews24
